list.abstract: by是一个基本词汇。意思是靠近，通过，作副词时表示经过，在旁边；作 介词时表示在……之前。常用形态的有prep.和adv.形式。

yingyinNormal.en: By making constipated moose sounds?
yingyinNormal.zh: 通过像便秘的驼鹿一样叫唤？

yingyinNormal.en: I've double my battery life, by scavenging Rover 1.
yingyinNormal.zh: 通过搜刮1号车，我把电量增加了一倍。

yingyinNormal.en: And of course she must improve her mind by extensive reading.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且她一定通过广泛的阅读 来扩展他的视野。

yingyinNormal.en: You can modify it to calculate our chance of having sex by changing the formula to use the number of single women in LA and the number of those I find attractive by what I call the Wolowitz coefficient.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你可以通过把数据改成洛城单身女人的数量和通过沃罗威茨系数计算出来天仙妹妹数量用来计算我们有爱可做的概率。

yingyinNormal.en: And I'm gonna really get in that brow action by just physically drawing the eyebrows.
yingyinNormal.zh: 接下来我通过画眉毛来开始画眉动作。

yingyinNormal.en: In fact, your acquisition by this program as well as the program itself has been reviewed and sanctioned by a military court.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，你大脑的使用权和整个项目都通过了军事法庭的审核。

yingyinNormal.en: They immunize themselves by rubbing against the tentacles from a very young age.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从幼鱼期开始它们就通过摩擦触手来自我免疫。

yingyinNormal.en: By adopting the most advanced transportation system in the world: high-speed rail.
yingyinNormal.zh: 通过使用这世界上最先进的交通运输系统：高铁。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, it occurs to me you could solve all your problems by obtaining more money.
yingyinNormal.zh: 依我看，你的所有问题都可以通过多挣点钱来解决。

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon, honey, did you ever consider making friends by being, I don't know, pleasant?
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿，亲爱的，你有没有考虑过通过让人开心来交友啊？

yingyinNormal.en: Excuse me, Your Honor. By denying petitioners' motion for specific performance...
yingyinNormal.zh: 抱歉，法官阁下，法庭通过驳回申请人关于履行特定义务的动议。

yingyinNormal.en: No, we turned our stereo down by sending a signal around the world via the internet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是，我们通过互联网走了地球一圈发送了一个命令把音响关小的。

yingyinNormal.en: That innovation is what made possible our modern consumer culture by enabling a low-unit cost for manufactured goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这项创新通过低成本的生产商品造就了现代消费文化。

yingyinNormal.en: Determining baseline fear levels in capuchin monkeys by measuring their response to visual stimuli.
yingyinNormal.zh: 通过测定僧帽猴对视觉刺激的反应，确定他们的恐惧基线水平。

yingyinNormal.en: The pressure that will be exerted on her body can be calculated by force divided by the area on the top of your arms that comes in contact with her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作用到她身上的压强可以通过压力，除以你双臂上表面与她身体发生接触的面积来得出。

yingyinNormal.en: It's just how much am I gonna learn about fashion by walking Mira, the arthritic seamstress, to the bathroom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但我怎么样才能通过扶得了关节炎的女裁缝上厕所来学习时尚？

yingyinNormal.en: The vote is eight to one in favor. However, as you know, we cannot proceed unless by unanimous vote.
yingyinNormal.zh: 结果是8票赞成，1票反对，如各位所知，只有全票赞成才能通过决议。

yingyinNormal.en: Its goal is to make me look guilty by association, but there are the way things look and the way things actually are.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其目的就是要通过关联让我看上去有罪，但表现与事实是两回事。

yingyinNormal.en: So we discussed how big the wormhole should be and agreed that it should be just barely big enough that it could be seen from Earth, through the bending of light around the Wormhole, by the wormhole's warped space.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以我们讨论了虫洞应该有多大，并同意它应该刚刚足够大，它应该能够从地球上看到，通过虫洞周围光的弯曲，通过虫洞扭曲的空间。

yingyinNormal.en: Our memories, they have to be passed down by those who knew us in life. In the stories they tell about us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的记忆得通过那些认识我们的人传下，去一个一个的故事传颂下去。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Huge profits are made <highlight>by</highlight> a few big firms who run the market places.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 巨额利润则由少数经营市场的大公司获得。

examination_example.sentence: Citizens still have a right to expect private documents to remain private and protected <highlight>by</highlight> the Constitution's prohibition on unreasonable searches.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公民仍然有权要求私人文件保持私密性，并受到宪法禁止不合理搜查的法令的保护。

examination_example.sentence: I don't like quotas either; they run counter to my belief in meritocracy, governance <highlight>by</highlight> the capable.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我也不喜欢配额；它们与我对精英管理、能者居之的治理的理念背道而驰。

examination_example.sentence: DeepMind must start <highlight>by</highlight> acknowledging that both sides mean well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: DeepMind必须首先承认双方的出发点都是好的。

examination_example.sentence: This is why repeated attempts at reform legislation have failed , leaving the Postal Service unable to pay its bills except <highlight>by</highlight> deferring vital modernization.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这就是为什么改革立法的多次尝试都以失败告终，使得邮政服务除非推迟重要的现代化否则无法支付账单。

examination_example.sentence: You could limit distractions <highlight>by</highlight> reading only physical books, or on single-purpose e-readers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你可以通过只看实体书或单一用途的电子阅读器来减少分心。

examination_example.sentence: The number of adults doing weekly sport did rise, <highlight>by</highlight> nearly 2 million in the run-up to 2012.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2012年之前，每周参加体育运动的成年人数量确实增加了近200万。

examination_example.sentence: Students who do not need the extra training could cut their debt mountain <highlight>by</highlight> a third.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不需要额外培训的学生可以将他们的债务减少三分之一。

examination_example.sentence: The number of social-science students worldwide has swollen <highlight>by</highlight> about 11% every year since 2000.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自2000年以来，全球的社会科学学生人数每年增长约11%。

examination_example.sentence: BMI equals body mass divided <highlight>by</highlight> the square of height.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 身体质量指数等于体重除以身高的平方。

examination_example.sentence: Up until a few decades ago, our visions of the future were largely — though <highlight>by</highlight> no means uniformly — glowingly positive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直到几十年前，我们对未来的愿景在很大程度上是乐观的，但绝不是一致的。

examination_example.sentence: It's especially vulnerable to light damage, and <highlight>by</highlight> the mid-1990s, Gilardi's pumpkins, roses, and other figures were splitting and crumbling.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它特别容易受到光的损害，到了20世纪90年代中期，吉拉蒂的南瓜、玫瑰和其他图案都开始开裂和破碎。

word_usage.usage:
by置于不带the的名词前，表示原因“由于……”
权威例句：They met by chance.他们不期而遇。
表示凭借、乘坐某种交通工具时，用by+交通工具，交通工具前不加冠词，在句中作方式状语
表达"通过做某事”要用by doing sth.来表示方式、方法、手段等，在句中做方式状语。而对by引导的介词短语作方式状语， 提问时用how。

by和take、hold等动词连用，说明接触身体的某一部分
权威例句：She took Gill by the hand.她拉起吉尔的手。

by放在反身代词前，译为“独自;独立（完成某事）”
例：I'm going to London by myself next week.我准备下星期一个人去伦敦。

direction_info.description:

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 增长(by后表示数量增加或减少的幅度)
顺便说说；顺便提起；在路上；在途中
大大地；…得多；显然；迄今为止
如今；到现在；截止到目前

examination_example.sentence: In pre-Classical Greece, for instance, people "corrected" official calendars <highlight>by</highlight> shifting dates forward or backward to reflect the change of season.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，在前古典时期的希腊，人们通过向前或向后移动日期来“修正”官方日历，以反映季节的变化。

examination_example.sentence: Recently, I took a trip home <highlight>by</highlight> train.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近，我乘火车回家旅行。

examination_example.sentence: If you want time to have breakfast with your family, save some time the night before <highlight>by</highlight> setting out clothes, shoes, and bags.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你想有时间和家人一起吃早餐，那就在前一天晚上准备好衣服、鞋子和包包。

examination_example.sentence: Your application will be accessed <highlight>by</highlight> UNESCO managers and will stay in our database for six months.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你的申请将被联合国教科文组织的管理人员访问，并将在我们的数据库中保存六个月。

examination_example.sentence: Vital to human life, art is celebrated and used <highlight>by</highlight> nations across the world for various purposes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 艺术对人类生活至关重要，世界各国出于各种目的庆祝和使用艺术。

examination_example.sentence: The environmental challenges are significant but the efforts made <highlight>by</highlight> the Tanzania National Park Authority seem to be paying off .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 环境挑战是巨大的，但是坦桑尼亚国家公园管理局所做的努力似乎得到了回报。

examination_example.sentence: One afternoon when I was in primary school, I was walking <highlight>by</highlight> the school playground.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我上小学的时候，有一天下午，我在学校操场边散步。

examination_example.sentence: We could probably just walk <highlight>by</highlight> the lake, and I'll ask Mike to join us.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们也许可以在湖边散步，我会叫迈克一起去。

examination_example.sentence: What percentage of student job seekers have found a job <highlight>by</highlight> now?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到目前为止，已找到工作的学生求职者的百分比是多少？

examination_example.sentence: The study also showed that just 20% of those who looked for jobs before graduation have found one <highlight>by</highlight> now.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究还显示，在毕业前找工作的人中，只有20%的人现在找到了工作。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> the way, do you also need me to drive you home tomorrow afternoon?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 顺便问一下，你明天下午还需要我开车送你回家吗？

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> the way, are you going to the concert tomorrow evening?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 顺便问一下，你明天晚上去听音乐会吗？

examination_example.sentence: I'll need to hear back from you <highlight>by</highlight> Wednesday.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我需要在星期三之前得到你的答复。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> last year, the Yellowstone wolf population had grown to more than 170 wolves.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到去年，黄石公园的狼数量已经增长到170多只。

examination_example.sentence: That is <highlight>by</highlight> design.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是有意的。

examination_example.sentence: That's very kind of you, but they've already left for their grandma's.You know, Suzy lives close <highlight>by</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你真好，但他们已经去奶奶家了。你知道，Suzy就住在附近。

examination_example.sentence: And Britain is <highlight>by</highlight> far the largest importer of tea in the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到目前为止，英国是世界上最大的茶叶进口国。

examination_example.sentence: This is compared to half of students who had looked for a job <highlight>by</highlight> this time two years ago.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，两年前的这个时候，有一半的学生已经找到了工作。

word_usage.usage: by意思是just at the side of （就在…旁边），因此 sth. that is by you 要比 sth. that is near you表示的距离离你更近。

by和with都可用来表示某人如何做某事，by用于动作；with用于一件工具、东西等：
He got what he wanted by talking very cleverly.
他话说得很巧妙因而得到了他想要的东西。
He got what he wanted with much money.
他用很多钱得到了自己想要的。

direction_info.description:

examination_example.sentence: Now people can pay <highlight>by</highlight> scanning(扫描）their faces while shopping.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在人们可以在购物时通过扫描脸来支付。

examination_example.sentence: Most waves are produced <highlight>by</highlight> winds.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数波浪是由风产生的。

examination_example.sentence: Last week, Jane went to London from China <highlight>by</highlight> plane.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 上周，简从中国乘飞机去了伦敦。

examination_example.sentence: On the 10th floor, she was greeted <highlight>by</highlight> John, the old man who interviewed her several days ago.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在10楼，她受到了约翰的迎接，就是几天前采访过她的那位老人。

examination_example.sentence: In 2014, she was accepted <highlight>by</highlight> Tianjin University and finally her dream came true.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2014年，她被天津大学录取，终于梦想成真。

examination_example.sentence: Cars and trucks controlled <highlight>by</highlight> AI may make the drivers lose their jobs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人工智能控制汽车和卡车可能会让司机失业。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> age 17, he was known for his talent in music.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 17岁时，他就以音乐天赋而闻名。

examination_example.sentence: The number of 5G SEPs rose to more than 60,000 globally <highlight>by</highlight> the end of April 2019, the report said．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 报道称，截至2019年4月底，全球5G SEPs（标准关键专利）数量已增至6万多台。

examination_example.sentence: They're digging, cutting leaves and planting new seeds (种子)，<highlight>by</highlight> summer, their gardens will be full of bright colours.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们挖土、剪叶、播种新种子，到了夏天，他们的花园将五彩缤纷。

examination_example.sentence: Nobody taught my grandpa how to use WeChat, so he learned it all <highlight>by</highlight> himself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没人教我爷爷怎么用微信，都是他自己学的。

examination_example.sentence: She got a seat <highlight>by</highlight> herself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她自己找了个座位。

examination_example.sentence: She printed the story <highlight>by</highlight> herself.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她自己发表了这个故事。

examination_example.sentence: A group of zebras ran <highlight>by</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一群斑马跑过。

examination_example.sentence: As time went <highlight>by</highlight>, I began to change my earlier simple judgement (评价).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着时间的流逝，我开始改变我早先简单的判断。

examination_example.sentence: If people often stop <highlight>by</highlight> for a talk, you may need to move to a different place.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果人们经常过来聊天，你可能需要换个地方。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> mid-morning, four kids were sculpting (雕塑) the sand alongside him.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 到上午10点左右，四个孩子在他旁边雕塑沙子。

examination_example.sentence: More than 50 percent of young people suffer back pain <highlight>by</highlight> their teenage years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 超过50%的年轻人在青少年时期就饱受背痛之苦。

examination_example.sentence: You might have neck and shoulder pain <highlight>by</highlight> doing that.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这样做，你可能会感到脖子和肩膀疼痛。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> law, you can't work more than 35 hours each week during school holidays.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据法律规定，在学校放假期间，你每周的工作时间不能超过35小时。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>By</highlight> the way, could you tell us where you heard about our company?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 顺便问一下，您能告诉我们您是从哪里听说我们公司的吗？

word_usage.usage: by+交通工具可以表示“乘...”，中间不能加冠词，如：by train; by bus; by bike等。注意：表示“步行”不能用by foot，要用on foot。

by用于被动结构时，既可以引出施动者，也可用来表示方式方法。
示例：(1) I was bitten by the the dog.
我被那只狗咬了。
(2) May I pay by cheque?
我能用支票付款吗？
